<component name="NrrdSetupTexture" category="NrrdData">
  <overview>
    <author>Michael Callahan
    </author>
    <summary>Set up a volume texture from a 3D scalar nrrd.</summary>
    <description>
    <p>Efficiently compute the inputs to NrrdTextureBuilder.  The
       first output port will contain a 4D nrrd where the fast dimension
       contains normals and values packed together (normal refers to the
       gradient.)  The second output will contain the gradient magnitudes.
       The first output will be of type unsigned character as expected
       by NrrdTextureBuilder.  The gradient magnitude field is of type float
       and should be run through UnuQuantize.</p>
    </description>
  </overview>
  <implementation>
  </implementation>
  <io>
    <inputs lastportdynamic="no">
      <port>
        <name>Value</name>
        <datatype>SCIRun::Nrrd</datatype>
      </port>
    </inputs>
    <outputs>
      <port>
        <name>Normal/Value</name>
        <datatype>SCIRun::Nrrd</datatype>
      </port>
      <port>
        <name>Gradient Magnitude</name>
        <datatype>SCIRun::Nrrd</datatype>
      </port>
    </outputs>
  </io>
  <gui>
    <parameter>
      <widget>Label</widget>
      <label>Autogenerated GUI explanation</label>
    </parameter>
  </gui>
  <testing>
  </testing>
</component>

